1
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:47,359
Tian Qing, don't touch it!

2
00:00:50,960 --> 00:00:51,640
What's wrong?

3
00:01:05,159 --> 00:01:05,959
Tian Qing!

4
00:01:09,079 --> 00:01:10,120
Tian Qing!

5
00:01:11,319 --> 00:01:12,120
Tian Qing!

6
00:01:12,599 --> 00:01:14,239
Tian Qing! Tian Qing! Tian Qing!

7
00:01:14,599 --> 00:01:16,480
Tian Qing! Tian Qing!

8
00:01:18,040 --> 00:01:19,760
Buddy, how is he?

9
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:24,760
These bugs...

10
00:01:24,959 --> 00:01:27,000
Living year-round in such extreme cold,

11
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:28,920
their genes have mutated.

12
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:31,239
They must've developed a neurotoxin

13
00:01:31,599 --> 00:01:33,920
to cause something like this.

14
00:01:34,519 --> 00:01:35,239
Godfather!

15
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:37,920
There's more and more of them!

16
00:01:38,239 --> 00:01:39,519
Old Chen, what do we do?

17
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:41,560
It's all that old white-haired geezer's fault!

18
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:43,920
He just had to push the ice wolf and trigger the trap.

19
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:45,439
Fire!

20
00:01:49,599 --> 00:01:51,400
Old Chen, this thing actually works!

21
00:01:51,599 --> 00:01:52,760
These bugs are scared of fire!

22
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:21,439
Hurry!

23
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,599
Avalanche!

24
00:02:22,599 --> 00:02:23,680
Hurry, push the lid open!

25
00:02:23,680 --> 00:02:24,240
Come on!

26
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:25,479
Give me a hand, hurry!

27
00:02:31,919 --> 00:02:32,400
Get down, quick!

28
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:33,560
Lu, hurry!

29
00:02:38,639 --> 00:02:39,280
Move!

30
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,120
Hurry, hurry!

31
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:41,599
Get down!

32
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:43,439
Fatty, down!

33
00:02:44,919 --> 00:02:46,159
Xiao Qi, you go first!

34
00:02:46,879 --> 00:02:47,560
Move!

35
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:50,639
Brother Chen, hurry!

36
00:02:54,479 --> 00:02:55,000
Pull!

37
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:21,840
Sure, we survived,

38
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,439
but what do we do now?

39
00:03:23,599 --> 00:03:24,719
There's an avalanche outside.

40
00:03:25,479 --> 00:03:26,759
The way back is blocked.

41
00:03:26,759 --> 00:03:27,759
We'll suffocate in here!

42
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:29,319
This place is huge.

43
00:03:29,319 --> 00:03:30,919
I refuse to believe we can't find an exit.

44
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:32,120
Let's get moving.

45
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:33,199
It's pretty dangerous here.

46
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:35,879
I agree.

47
00:03:35,919 --> 00:03:38,159
We're about to find the gate of Mengna Valley.

48
00:03:38,159 --> 00:03:39,719
Let's push through in one go!

49
00:03:56,479 --> 00:03:57,199
Adviser He.

50
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:03,280
These Jueda people really love abyss culture.

51
00:04:03,319 --> 00:04:04,599
Look at how they dug this place out.

52
00:04:05,159 --> 00:04:05,800
So deep,

53
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,520
so cold, so gloomy.

54
00:04:10,719 --> 00:04:12,639
Since the Bingpo Guardian Mountain

55
00:04:12,840 --> 00:04:14,439
guards the gate of Mengna Valley,

56
00:04:14,719 --> 00:04:15,680
then this place

57
00:04:15,680 --> 00:04:17,879
must be the path to the Gate of Cataclysm.

58
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:18,879
Past the Gate of Cataclysm,

59
00:04:18,879 --> 00:04:20,040
that should be Mengna Valley, right?

60
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:20,839
It should be.

61
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:23,079
It must be the capital of Mengna Valley,

62
00:04:23,079 --> 00:04:24,759
called Chiyan Jizhou.

63
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:28,000
What "Chi"? What "Yan"?

64
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,279
I think

65
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,920
what we should really celebrate

66
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:32,600
is our spirit of adventure.

67
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,319
For that alone,

68
00:04:33,319 --> 00:04:35,199
Commander Chen owes me a hot pot dinner.

69
00:04:36,959 --> 00:04:38,079
Old Chen, Old Chen, Old Chen! Godfather!

70
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:39,319
What are you doing?

71
00:04:39,319 --> 00:04:40,120
Have you lost your mind?

72
00:04:40,199 --> 00:04:40,759
Chen Youxi!

73
00:04:40,759 --> 00:04:42,160
Don't move! Do you want to die?

74
00:04:42,639 --> 00:04:43,399
Godfather!

75
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:46,639
What's going on, Old Chen?

76
00:04:48,319 --> 00:04:48,720
What happened?

77
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,839
Xiao Qi is dead.

78
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:01,800
Xiao Qi.

79
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:04,240
Looks like...

80
00:05:04,879 --> 00:05:05,439
it's too late.

81
00:05:05,439 --> 00:05:06,439
Listen to me.

82
00:05:07,079 --> 00:05:08,519
I worked for Uncle Min

83
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,560
because he kidnapped my fourth uncle.

84
00:05:10,839 --> 00:05:13,399
He'd already heard Lu tip off An Xiang,

85
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:15,399
so he had me wait there early

86
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:16,439
to intercept you.

87
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:17,959
Dawang got kidnapped?

88
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:19,160
When did this happen?

89
00:05:19,439 --> 00:05:20,759
The moment you all split up,

90
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,560
he grabbed my fourth uncle.

91
00:05:24,399 --> 00:05:25,680
He threatened me,

92
00:05:25,879 --> 00:05:27,720
saying I had to bring him back safely.

93
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,439
Otherwise...

94
00:05:29,160 --> 00:05:30,720
Otherwise... otherwise...

95
00:05:31,319 --> 00:05:32,040
Hang in there.

96
00:05:33,959 --> 00:05:34,759
Uncle Min...

97
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,360
his eyes...

98
00:05:36,639 --> 00:05:40,399
are the greediest, foulest eyes I've ever seen.

99
00:05:41,319 --> 00:05:43,399
You have to be careful.

100
00:05:44,319 --> 00:05:45,399
Chen... Chen...

101
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:47,399
Brother Chen...

102
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:08,120
If that's the case,

103
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:09,920
then Xiao Qi here

104
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:12,279
had no choice either.

105
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:15,160
He's always treated Old Chen like a brother.

106
00:06:15,439 --> 00:06:16,240
Commander Chen.

107
00:06:16,519 --> 00:06:17,240
If you ask me,

108
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:19,240
we should leave these people here

109
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,439
and let them fend for themselves.

110
00:06:20,439 --> 00:06:21,360
I dare you to try.

111
00:06:24,519 --> 00:06:25,439
Have you all lost your minds?

112
00:06:25,519 --> 00:06:26,360
Is this a mutiny?

113
00:06:26,839 --> 00:06:27,600
Xiao Qi said,

114
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:29,439
if anything happened to him,

115
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,240
I should listen to you.

116
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:34,519
I'm a businessman.

117
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:36,920
Minimizing risk in what I do

118
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:38,040
can't be wrong, can it?

119
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,480
Holding Dawang

120
00:06:41,279 --> 00:06:44,680
was just to give myself extra insurance.

121
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,160
What's wrong with that?

122
00:06:46,399 --> 00:06:48,439
We agreed to go all the way to Mengna Valley

123
00:06:48,839 --> 00:06:50,480
and find the Lingxiao Pearl, right?

124
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:52,800
I put up the money, you put in the work.

125
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,399
Fair and square,

126
00:06:54,399 --> 00:06:55,160
isn't it?

127
00:06:55,279 --> 00:06:57,040
Right, right, he paid for it.

128
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:58,040
The hell it's fair.

129
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:58,800
Insane.

130
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,560
Fair?

131
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:01,040
Outside the tent,

132
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:03,240
when he had a knife, a weapon,

133
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:04,000
threatening us,

134
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,120
did he say it was fair then?

135
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,199
Right.

136
00:07:06,199 --> 00:07:07,399
So what do you want to do?

137
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:09,600
We didn't kill Xiao Qi.

138
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:11,079
You didn't kill Xiao Qi,

139
00:07:11,279 --> 00:07:12,480
but you threatened him

140
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:13,560
into betraying his friends.

141
00:07:14,199 --> 00:07:15,040
So?

142
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:19,160
So our contract

143
00:07:19,439 --> 00:07:20,879
doesn't include hurting friends.

144
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,240
From this moment on,

145
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:24,720
it ends here.

146
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,279
We part ways.

147
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:28,639
Let's go.

148
00:07:51,759 --> 00:07:53,399
There's only one path in and out.

149
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,240
Talk about going separate ways,

150
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,279
but it's not that easy.

151
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,240
In a little while,

152
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:59,120
he'll come crawling back to us.

153
00:07:59,120 --> 00:07:59,800
If he dares come,

154
00:07:59,879 --> 00:08:01,160
I won't go easy on him.

155
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,079
Come on, Fatty.

156
00:08:03,839 --> 00:08:05,360
This place is dangerous.

157
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,639
They don't even have weapons to defend themselves.

158
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:09,040
And there's a young woman with them.

159
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,279
What if, you know...

160
00:08:10,279 --> 00:08:11,079
something happens?

161
00:08:11,399 --> 00:08:12,439
You're just worried about An Xiang.

162
00:08:12,439 --> 00:08:13,399
Then have her come with you.

163
00:08:13,399 --> 00:08:14,360
See if she will.

164
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:17,000
The way you're talking,

165
00:08:17,319 --> 00:08:19,120
I really don't like it.

166
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,160
You don't like it?

167
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,319
Then deal with it.

168
00:08:21,439 --> 00:08:23,120
If you hadn't tipped An Xiang off,

169
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,519
and let that old fool overhear,

170
00:08:24,519 --> 00:08:25,879
we'd have split up long ago.

171
00:08:26,279 --> 00:08:27,160
Was that really necessary?

172
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:29,000
Xiao Qi held it in the whole time,

173
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,600
and only told the truth before dying.

174
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,039
Why don't you think about that?

175
00:08:32,519 --> 00:08:33,679
That's all in the past.

176
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,159
Stop bringing it up.

177
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,759
I'm sick of it too.

178
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,159
Just drop it.

179
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:39,679
Shut your mouth.

180
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:40,879
I'm sick of hearing you talk.

181
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:43,960
One bite from a tiny bug can kill you.

182
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:49,759
Going any further,

183
00:08:53,519 --> 00:08:55,039
we have no way back.

184
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:56,799
So stop saying things like

185
00:08:56,799 --> 00:08:58,440
you're afraid of being a burden.

186
00:09:04,639 --> 00:09:05,519
Brother Lu!

187
00:09:06,399 --> 00:09:07,200
Wait up!

188
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:08,159
Wait up!

189
00:09:08,159 --> 00:09:08,759
She's caught up.

190
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,960
Sister Shutong, Brother Chen,

191
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:16,320
please forgive my godfather.

192
00:09:16,399 --> 00:09:17,559
Everything he's done,

193
00:09:17,759 --> 00:09:19,639
it's all to find Mengna Valley quickly,

194
00:09:19,639 --> 00:09:21,240
and unlock the secret of the Lingxiao Pearl.

195
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:24,519
Because he really doesn't have much time left.

196
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,559
What? What do you mean?

197
00:09:26,559 --> 00:09:28,039
How is he running out of time?

198
00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:29,960
Brother Chen should know.

199
00:09:30,919 --> 00:09:32,799
The scar on my godfather's back,

200
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,759
it's already spread to his neck,

201
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,679
and all over his arms.

202
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:39,120
He doesn't have the strength anymore

203
00:09:39,159 --> 00:09:41,120
to do anything else to you.

204
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,120
I'm sorry.

205
00:09:43,519 --> 00:09:44,840
I'm begging you.

206
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:47,279
I apologize on my godfather's behalf.

207
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:55,279
Let me tell you,

208
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,240
it's only because we're deep in the wilderness.

209
00:09:57,519 --> 00:09:58,799
If we were out in the world,

210
00:09:58,879 --> 00:09:59,879
no question about it,

211
00:09:59,879 --> 00:10:01,559
he'd be hauled straight to the police station.

212
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,399
He'd have to face legal punishment.

213
00:10:16,519 --> 00:10:18,720
Please forgive my godfather.

214
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:22,000
All right, all right.

215
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:25,159
If no one has any objections,

216
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:26,720
then it's settled.

217
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:27,559
Go back and get your dad.

218
00:10:27,559 --> 00:10:28,399
Come along with us.

219
00:10:28,399 --> 00:10:28,960
Hurry, go get him.

220
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:29,679
Really?

221
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:33,600
Thank you, thank you, Brother Lu.

222
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:40,759
She got what she wanted.

223
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:43,080
Aren't you going to check on your father-in-law?

224
00:10:46,559 --> 00:10:47,600
I'm going to scout the path.

225
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:51,679
So... so petty.

226
00:10:55,120 --> 00:10:55,919
Unbelievable.

227
00:10:58,639 --> 00:11:00,000
Come on, hurry up.

228
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:25,159
I wanted to tell you,

229
00:11:26,559 --> 00:11:28,080
but so much happened along the way,

230
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:30,679
I didn't get the chance.

231
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:36,639
Don't be angry.

232
00:11:41,799 --> 00:11:42,799
I'm not angry.

233
00:11:46,679 --> 00:11:48,080
I just want you to stay alive.

234
00:12:20,039 --> 00:12:22,399
This is truly a wonder of the world.

235
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:26,440
What... what are all these paintings?

236
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:30,639
This must be a ceremony of the Jueda people.

237
00:12:32,399 --> 00:12:33,960
They opened the Gate of Cataclysm.

238
00:12:34,159 --> 00:12:37,440
And used these paintings to record their great deeds.

239
00:12:38,519 --> 00:12:40,320
So this is the Gate of Cataclysm.

240
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:49,480
Lu, I'll go scout ahead.

241
00:12:49,759 --> 00:12:50,279
Keep an eye on him.

242
00:12:50,279 --> 00:12:51,360
Don't let him cause trouble again.

243
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,120
Come on, take a break.

244
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,399
What are you studying?

245
00:13:05,440 --> 00:13:06,440
Look at this painting.

246
00:13:06,679 --> 00:13:07,759
It has four layers.

247
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:10,200
I have no idea what it means.

248
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:12,120
So I want to record it.

249
00:13:13,759 --> 00:13:14,960
The first layer...

250
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:18,159
Why is this woman covering her face?

251
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:23,519
What does this snake on the second layer mean?

252
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:28,840
The third layer seems to have been deliberately damaged.

253
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:31,200
From the outline, it's circular.

254
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:33,399
Could it be the eyeball pattern?

255
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:34,519
It's possible.

256
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:40,120
Is the fourth one a statue or a person?

257
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:42,960
What do these four pictures mean?

258
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:45,600
This giant serpent...

259
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:48,399
I think it's a totem of the Jueda people.

260
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:52,679
As for this woman and the figure,

261
00:13:54,799 --> 00:13:57,519
it must be a scene from one of their ceremonies.

262
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:00,080
And this eyeball pattern...

263
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:01,519
Based on our experiences in Yunling

264
00:14:01,519 --> 00:14:03,080
and Nanyun before,

265
00:14:04,039 --> 00:14:05,440
wherever there's an eyeball pattern,

266
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,120
there's a Lingxiao Pearl.

267
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:09,360
So I think

268
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,600
we're getting closer and closer to the truth.

269
00:14:15,919 --> 00:14:16,799
How's it going, Old Chen?

270
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:18,159
Look, look.

271
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:21,080
Is there a path?

272
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:22,600
No, no, no path.

273
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:23,879
And no ice either.

274
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:26,240
Yes, yes, yes.

275
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:27,080
That's the one.

276
00:14:29,159 --> 00:14:31,159
This place is lower than the glacier.

277
00:14:31,559 --> 00:14:33,320
So the temperature is suitable.

278
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:34,840
What's more,

279
00:14:35,159 --> 00:14:36,720
even though we're at the bottom of the abyss,

280
00:14:36,879 --> 00:14:38,480
light still comes through.

281
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:40,759
So it's no surprise that plants can grow here.

282
00:14:40,799 --> 00:14:41,759
I'm thinking,

283
00:14:42,080 --> 00:14:43,559
could it be this wall?

284
00:14:44,240 --> 00:14:46,120
Let's focus our efforts on this wall.

285
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:47,519
Maybe it's right behind the wall.

286
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:48,679
Fatty.

287
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:49,759
There's no ice over there.

288
00:14:49,759 --> 00:14:50,480
None.

289
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:54,600
This ice wall extends to the ice beneath our feet.

290
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:56,440
There's probably an underground river below.

291
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:57,919
And these plants

292
00:14:58,320 --> 00:15:00,039
mean the ice layer can't be that thick.

293
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:01,279
We chisel through the ice,

294
00:15:01,279 --> 00:15:02,720
find the underground river below,

295
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:05,559
and swim under the ice wall along the river.

